<p>
The Spread Execution Model seeks to fill orders when the bid-ask spread is lower than a set percentage of asset price (default: 0.5%). The intent is to avoid extreme slippage. Since bid/ask price data is only available in minute/second/tick resolution, the model will only support these resolution during market opening hours/</p>
<p>To use the pre-made Execution Model in your algorithm, you should set it in Initialize():</p>
<div class="section-example-container">
	<pre class="csharp">SetExecution( new SpreadExecutionModel() );</pre>
	<pre class="python">self.SetExecution( SpreadDeviationExecutionModel() )</pre>
</div>
<p>This model has the following optional parameters:</p>
<div class="section-example-container">
	<pre class="all">SpreadExecutionModel( acceptingSpreadPercent=0.005 )</pre>
</div>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li><code>acceptingSpreadPercent</code> - Maximum acceptable bid-ask spread in percentage of asset price to place an order.
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>

<p class="csharp">You can view the complete C# <i>implementation</i> of this model in <a href="https://github.com/QuantConnect/Lean/blob/master/Algorithm.Framework/Execution/SpreadExecutionModel.cs" target="_BLANK">GitHub</a>.</p>
<p class="python">You can view the complete Python <i>implementation</i> of this model in <a href="https://github.com/QuantConnect/Lean/blob/master/Algorithm.Framework/Execution/SpreadExecutionModel.py" target="_BLANK">GitHub</a>.</p>
